    {
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 3,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Router Intelligence Overview\nPrimary routing is now formula-driven on every Prometheus-backed decision.\n\n- Fast path = NMT\n- Heavy path = LLM\n- Heavy path is **not** modeled as `NMT + LLM`\n- The router compares the smaller weighted score using Prometheus base queueing terms plus per-request `p_llm` penalties\n- `approx_score_nmt_seconds` and `approx_score_llm_seconds` are unweighted base scores only\n- Threshold-based routing remains available only when the router falls back to local queue-depth logic\n\nFeature panels below expose exact existing proxies already computed by the router runtime: `source_length_words`, `log_perplexity`, and `perplexity_per_word`.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "About This Dashboard",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
